                <p style="text-align: left">
                  <span style="font-size: 9pt"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif">
 
Welcome to our latest Bottom Line Thinking mailing – the first since our formal name change to AECOM at the end of last year. 2014 looks to be a key year for property owners and occupiers: a rising market, the full impact of the FA2012 fixtures changes, R22 and the Energy Act are key considerations; all against the backdrop of the run-up to the 2015 General Election.
<br /><br />
Tax is never far from the domestic or political agenda and our latest mailing includes our take on some of the issues that those involved in the property sector face.  Our bespoke guidelines will help you to be prepared for the obligations imposed by the FA2012 fixtures changes.  We’d be pleased to see you at one of our popular regional seminars next month, further details of which are below.
</span></span></p>
                <p style="text-align: left">
                  <span style="font-size: 9pt"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif">If there are any particular topics you would like to see addressed in future mailings, we would like to hear from you: <a href=mailto:Fiscalincentivesteam.europe@aecom.com>Fiscalincentivesteam.europe@aecom.com</a></span></span></p>
                <p style="text-align: left">
                  <span style="font-size: 9pt"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif">
<b>Changes to BPRA Scheme Confirmed</b></span></span><br />
                  <span style="font-size: 9pt"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif">The draft Finance Bill 2014 contains proposed changes to the rules for claiming Business Premises Renovation Allowances (BPRA). These changes will impact the quantum and timing of qualifying expenditure which will undoubtedly reduce the attractiveness of the scheme to private equity investors. [<span style="font-size: 9pt"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="http://media.bankingtaxfinance.com/App_Media/DavisLangdon/pdf/Changes_to_BPRA_Scheme_-_Final.pdf">More</a>]</span></span></span></span></p>
                <p style="text-align: left">
                  <span style="font-size: 9pt"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif"><b>The Accountant and Capital Allowances on Property Acquisitions</b></span></span><br />
                  <span style="font-size: 9pt"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif">Changes to the fixtures rules introduced by Finance Act 2012 will take full effect from April 2014. The implications of the changes mean that current owners may lose the potential benefit of capital allowances to purchasers, and future owners, even if no prior claim for allowances has been made. Current owners are likely to be wholly reliant on their professional advisors to ensure that their entitlement is not compromised through inadequate due-diligence or poorly-drafted contract provisions. 
 [<span style="font-size: 9pt"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="http://media.bankingtaxfinance.com/App_Media/DavisLangdon/pdf/The_Accountant_and_CA_on_Property_Acquisitions_-_Final.pdf">More</a>]</span></span></span></span></p>
                <p style="text-align: left">
                  <span style="font-size: 9pt"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif"><b>R22 Replacement</b></span></span><br />
                  <span style="font-size: 9pt"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif">Businesses that depend on air conditioning, process chilling and industrial refrigeration equipment that contain R22 refrigerant have some important decisions to make to comply with current legislation. It is now illegal (from 1 January 2010) to use ‘virgin’ R22 refrigerant to top up existing installations. This ban will be expanded to recycled R22 from the 1 January 2014. [<span style="font-size: 9pt"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="http://media.bankingtaxfinance.com/App_Media/DavisLangdon/pdf/Copy_1_R22_Replacement_-_Are_You_Ready_for_Change_-_Readover_by_SPW2.pdf">More</a></span></span>]&nbsp;</span></span></p>
                <p style="text-align: left">
                  <span style="font-size: 9pt"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif"><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt">BOTTOM LINE TALKING</span></strong><br />
                  We are running a series of regional seminars in which we will discuss in more detail the current issues raised in thearticles above.</span></span></p>
                <p style="text-align: left">
                  <span style="font-size: 9pt"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif"><strong>To register, please click <a href="http://www.bankingtaxfinance.com/seminars/capital-allowances-the-fixture-rules-and-other-changes-update-for-occupiers-and-advisors.aspx">here</a></strong></span></span></p>
                <p style="text-align: left">
                  <span style="font-size: 9pt"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif">You can read more on this and related topics at: <a href="http://www.bankingtaxfinance.com/news.aspx">http://www.bankingtaxfinance.com/news.aspx</a></span></span></p>
